        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:52PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 652 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over North Druid Hills, or
near Decatur, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Decatur, Peachtree Corners, Sandy Springs, Roswell, Johns
Creek, Alpharetta, Dunwoody, Duluth, Suwanee, Lilburn, Chamblee,
Norcross, Doraville, Clarkston, Stone Mountain, Avondale Estates,
Berkeley Lake, Pine Lake, and Tucker.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
